# Method-call intent comments (shakti-game-engine)

In non-trivial functions (services, repositories, LLM wiring, session lifecycle), add a **short end-of-line comment** on meaningful calls explaining **what the callee does** or **why** it runs there—not a repeat of the function name.

- Prefer comments on **I/O** (`repository`, `llm_preparer`, `events.append`) and **domain transitions** (`session.start`, `record_evaluation`, `recompute_total_points`).
- Skip comments on obvious pure helpers (`unwrap`, trivial getters).
- Keep comments one line; no essays.

This complements structured logging (`user_id`, `trace_id`): comments clarify **control flow**, logs clarify **correlation**.
